# SECTION 5: INFRASTRUCTURE

## File System Layout (volumes)
- DATABASE_URL=/app/data/app.db
- ARTIFACTS_DIR=/app/volumes/artifacts   (named Docker volume — persisted)
- JOBS_WORKDIR=/app/volumes/jobs         (ephemeral — NOT a named volume)
- WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL=2                 (seconds, from env)
- NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
- NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8000

## Intermediate Directory Structure (per job)
/jobs/{job_id}/
├── raw/       # Module 1 output (original DOM + assets)
├── cleaned/   # Module 1 output (after strip trackers/fonts/comments)
├── mutated/   # Module 2 output (after CSS obfuscation + DOM noise)
└── rewritten/ # Module 3 copies mutated/ here; Module 4 edits images in-place;
               # Module 5 packs this entire dir into ZIP

## Dockerfile Rules
- Base image: python:3.12-slim.
- Node.js (nodejs + npm) installed via apt-get — no separate node stage.
- playwright install --with-deps chromium (exact command).
- COPY migrations/ ./migrations/  MUST be present (GAP-A).
- mkdir -p /app/data /app/volumes/artifacts /app/volumes/jobs
- EXPOSE 8000 3000
- CMD ["./entrypoint.sh"]

## entrypoint.sh Rules
- Uses bash & + wait. No supervisord.
- uvicorn backend.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 &
- cd /app/frontend && npm run start -- --port 3000 --hostname 0.0.0.0 &
- trap handles SIGTERM/SIGINT → kill both PIDs.
- wait -n exits when either process dies.

## docker-compose.yml Rules
- Single service 'app'.
- Named volumes: sqlite_data:/app/data, artifacts_data:/app/volumes/artifacts.
- JOBS_WORKDIR (/app/volumes/jobs) intentionally NOT a named volume (ephemeral).
- restart: unless-stopped
- env_file: .env for production deployment.

## Known Limitations (DO NOT try to fix these in MVP)
- [KNOWN_LIMITATION] Multi-page landings: only index.html is processed. Secondary HTML
  files are included in ZIP unprocessed.
- [KNOWN_LIMITATION] Pipeline resume on crash not supported. EC-16 resets to failed.
- [KNOWN_LIMITATION] JS string concatenation class replacement not supported (no AST parser).
  Only the 6 JS_REPLACE_PATTERNS are handled.
- [FUTURE] aggression_level per-job parameter.
- [FUTURE] Multiple parallel workers (Celery/ARQ).
- [FUTURE] Custom user prompts for AI module.
